1. SERIES ARCHITECTURE & NARRATIVE
The Memory Systems series is built on a single governing question: what memory infrastructure is required for reliable AI agents in enterprise systems? Every experiment, every article, every paper answers one facet of this question and builds on the last.
The series begins with Experiment 0 — proving that memory matters at all — and escalates through increasingly sophisticated infrastructure questions. By Experiment 5, you are addressing the hardest unsolved problem in production multi-agent systems: shared memory coordination without contamination.

	Each experiment must earn the right to the next one. Experiment 0 proves memory matters. Only then does Experiment 1's architecture comparison have stakes.

