EXPERIMENT 0
Foundation: Do Memory-Enabled Agents Outperform Stateless Agents?
Memory Layer · Working + Episodic + Semantic · Text-to-SQL Primary Domain

Hypothesis
Memory-enabled agents measurably outperform stateless agents on multi-turn enterprise tasks, with the performance gap widening with task complexity — but providing negligible benefit on single-turn, context-independent queries.

Why This Matters for Enterprise
Before any architecture comparison is worth making, the foundational premise must be proven: that memory produces a measurable benefit on tasks that actually occur in enterprise environments. Text-to-SQL is the ideal primary domain because it has ground truth — you can objectively score generated SQL against correct SQL without LLM-as-judge subjectivity. Every VP of Analytics has experienced the failure mode where an agent loses context between turns. This experiment quantifies that failure precisely.

