EXPERIMENT 1
Memory Backend Benchmark: Vector DB vs Graph DB vs Hybrid
Memory Architecture Layer · Pinecone · Weaviate · Neo4j · ChromaDB

Hypothesis
A hybrid memory architecture combining vector DB semantic search with a knowledge graph for relational context outperforms either approach alone by ≥25% on enterprise retrieval tasks, while adding <20ms latency overhead.

Why This Matters for Enterprise
Once E0 proves memory matters, the next question is which memory backend produces the best results. This is the question most engineering teams face when building their first enterprise memory system. The answer is not obvious — vector DBs excel at semantic similarity but struggle with relational queries; knowledge graphs excel at traversal but require structured data; hybrid architectures theoretically combine both strengths. This experiment quantifies the actual tradeoffs across realistic enterprise retrieval scenarios.

