EXPERIMENT 3
Retrieval Quality: Sparse vs Dense vs Re-ranking Pipelines
Memory Retrieval Layer · RAGAS · Pinecone · Cohere Rerank · BGE-M3

Hypothesis
A two-stage retrieval pipeline (dense retrieval + cross-encoder re-ranking with domain-adaptive thresholds) achieves F1 >0.87 on enterprise memory retrieval, outperforming single-stage approaches by ≥18%.

Why This Matters for Enterprise
Memory is only as good as what gets retrieved. An agent with perfect storage but poor retrieval behaves like a stateless agent — it cannot surface the right memory at the right time. This experiment tests 5 retrieval pipeline configurations across a 100K-document enterprise corpus, including domain transfer (trained on one domain, evaluated on another) — a critical real-world scenario that most retrieval benchmarks ignore.

